  * Leading Edge Technology meets Education 
  * Salary $100,577 - $111,748 + super 
  * Full time continuing | flexible working arrangements available. 

The purpose of the ICT Officer position is to provide high level technical
support in the delivery and operation of information systems and services
provided to the Brisbane Catholic Education schools and office communities. As
we continue to expand BCE are looking for an ICT Officer to join our
Information Technology Services Team and support our device management with
about 6500 Wireless access points, 2500 switches and 80,000 end user devices
you will support a large network of devices and users.

** About the role: **

  * Provide high level technical support in the delivery and operation of information systems and services 
  * Support and enhance the platforms and services provided by the School Technology team. 
  * Provide advice and support with major technologies include Cisco/Meraki wired and wireless networks, VMware Workspace ONE, Microsoft Server, and client operating systems (Windows, MacOS & iOS). 
  * Undertake high level analysis, development, administration, user support and operational activities. 

** About you: ** To be successful in this role you will demonstrate 

  * IT or related degree qualifications and /or industry qualifications relating to a complex ICT environment preferred. 
  * Proven experience in developing for and supporting enterprise level applications 
  * Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to troubleshoot complex technical issues independently. 
  * Effective communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work across teams and communicate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders. 
  * Experience with a range of software development methodologies, languages, and platforms. 

** All BCE employees will be: **

  * [ eligible to work in Australia ](https://www.bne.catholic.edu.au/bce-employment/app-info-and-assistance/Pages/Eligibility-to-work-in-Australia.aspx)
  * Hold or be eligible to hold a Positive Notice Blue card work working with children. 
  * Have a commitment to [ Safeguarding ](https://www.bne.catholic.edu.au/aboutus/Documents/Safeguarding%20commitment%20and%20stopline%20poster%20for%20Brisbane%20Catholic%20Education.pdf)
  * Provide proof of identity at the interview as part of the pre employment screening process 

For more detail, please refer to the attached Role Description.

  
  
